	<section id="sect-SPICE_Log_Files">
		<title>SPICE Log Files</title> 
		<para>
			SPICE log files are useful when troubleshooting SPICE connection issues. To start SPICE debugging, change the log level to <literal>debugging</literal>. Then, identify the log location.
		</para>
		<para>
			Both the clients used to access the guest machines and the guest machines themselves have SPICE log files. For client side logs, if a SPICE client was launched using the native client, for which a <filename>console.vv</filename> file is downloaded, use the <command>remote-viewer</command> command to enable debugging and generate log output.
		</para>
